The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 10: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee may meet state finance ministers this week to discuss their requirements from the budget. The implementation of the proposed goods and services tax, speculated to be delayed by over six months, is also likely to be discussed during the meeting. The finance minister will meet state finance ministers on January 13 as a pre-budget exercise, an official said.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 10: The government has set up a high-level committee, headed by Sam Pitroda and Deepak Parekh, to look into the factors affecting BSNLs financial health and give recommendations within a month. This was decided at a meeting chaired by Prime Minister Manmohan Singh last week.                             
	 New Delhi, Jan. 10: Posco has been asked by the environment ministry to take the consent of local tribals, as required under the forest rights act, before starting its proposed steel project in Orissa. Posco has received clearance from the ministry last month for acquiring forest land for its 12-million-tonne steel project.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 10: Steel consumption rose 7.7 per cent to 40.98 million tonnes during the April-December period of this fiscal compared with 38.04 million tonnes in the same period a year ago. Consumption rose on improved demand from automobile and consumer durables.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 10: Life insurance companies have appointed around 13 lakh agents during 2008-09. The number of life insurance agents increased to 29.37 lakh by the end of March 2009, according to the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority annual report.                            
	 Mumbai, Jan. 10: IBM plans to focus more on the services sector by scaling up its BPO operations in India. The company will hire 5,000 staff this year to support the expansion.                             
	 Mumbai, Jan. 10: Mukesh Ambani-led Reliance Retail has prepared a new business model, under which it will open small outlets at the premises of large companies.
                                                                                                                          
